Heat Exchanger Performance Analysis using Python

Project Overview
This project focuses on analyzing the performance of a heat exchanger using basic principles of heat transfer. The analysis is performed using Python by processing temperature and flow rate data to calculate heat transfer rates and effectiveness.

Objectives

Calculate heat transfer rate (Q) for hot and cold fluids
Determine the effectiveness (ε) of the heat exchanger
Visualize performance using graphs
Understand basic heat exchanger behavior through data analysis

Concepts Used

Heat Transfer
Energy Balance
Effectiveness of Heat Exchanger
Basic Thermodynamics

Dataset
The dataset contains:

Hot fluid inlet and outlet temperatures
Cold fluid inlet and outlet temperatures
Mass flow rates

Example data row:
Th_in = 80, Th_out = 60, Tc_in = 30, Tc_out = 45, m_hot = 1, m_cold = 1

Methodology

Heat Transfer Calculation
Heat transfer rate is calculated using:
Q = m × Cp × ΔT

Where:
m = mass flow rate (kg/s)
Cp = specific heat capacity (J/kg·K)
ΔT = temperature difference

Effectiveness Calculation
Effectiveness is calculated using:
ε = Q_actual / Q_max

Where:
Q_max = C_min × (Th_in − Tc_in)

Tools and Technologies

Python
pandas (data handling)
numpy (calculations)
matplotlib (visualization)

Results
The project generates:

Heat transfer rate (Q) for each dataset
Effectiveness (ε) of the heat exchanger
Graphs of heat transfer and effectiveness
